Title: Our future in cities
Description: Humanity's future is the future of cities. Explore the crowded favelas, greened-up blocks and futuristic districts that could shape the future of cities — and take a profane, hilarious side trip to the suburbs.

Title: The most popular TED Talks of 2018
Description: What. A. Year. These 25 TED Talks helped us make better decisions, taught us some fascinating science, gave us some hope for humanity and showed us what it's like to climb 3,000 feet ... without a rope.

Title: Legends of the design world
Description: Some of history's greatest designers share intriguing perspectives and vignettes from their prolific journeys.

Title: How do you solve a problem like the climate crisis?
Description: We all know about the climate crisis. We all want to stay informed — but the information can be overwhelming. Watch these talks to hear what’s at stake and find out what's being done.

Title: The power of film
Description: 12 visionary creators and curators — from Hollywood, Bollywood and Nollywood — talk about how to make movie magic.

Title: The most translated TED Talks
Description: A thoughtful selection of engaging TED Talks, translated into 40+ languages thanks to our wonderful TED Translators community!

Title: The art of the interview
Description: Glean interview skills and incredible insights from some of the greatest minds to sit down on the TED stage.

Title: The most popular talks of 2019
Description: Which TED Talks were watched most in 2019? These talks reflect a year defined by fighting for what's right, believing in the good despite all the bad, supporting others and yourself — and hoping for the best in the decade to come.

Title: The global power shift
Description: Big-picture talks about global politics and the shifting weight of the world.

Title: TED Talks by women leaders
Description: Who should run more of the world? Women. Until then, enjoy these talks by awesome women who lead fiercely and fearlessly.

Title: How to sustain meaningful relationships (near and far)
Description: These talks can help guide you in nurturing close, meaningful bonds with a long-distance partner, family, a new acquaintance or anyone in between.

Title: Planes, trains, automobiles — and jet suits?
Description: Innovators in transportation show that getting from point A to point B doesn't have to be boring.

Title: The big picture
Description: Must-listen talks about the future of the environment, crime, technology, government and the human race.

Title: Way, way out there
Description: Travel across the universe (or is it universes?) to see stunning images of Saturn's rings, hear haunting sounds from distant black holes and catch an infectious sense of wonder about galaxies far, far away.

Title: Interview with a business mogul
Description: Gain insights, wisdom and advice from visionaries at the top of their fields and industries.

Title: TED MacArthur Grant winners
Description: A collection of talks from creative individuals striving to bring light to some of the world's most pressing issues.

Title: Will drones save us or destroy us?
Description: Depending on who you listen to, drones will either save the world — or usher in our techno-driven doom. Here, take a look at the light and dark side of drones. See exclusive articles on the TED blog.

Title: An Introduction to TED Talks
Description: Welcome to the global archive of TED Talks! To dive in, start with these popular talks.

Title: Bill Gates: My 13 favorite talks
Description: When we asked Bill Gates to curate a list of his favorite talks, his first response was, “There are too many to pick, really.” Here, he's whittled it down to 13 essentials.

Title: TED Talks en Español
Description: ¡Ideas en nuestro idioma! TED Talks in Spanish, with subtitles in English and other languages.

Title: Personal tales from the edge of life
Description: Beautiful, intimate and ultimately uplifting stories of challenge — from making a new home in a strange country, to rebuilding life after unthinkable tragedy.

Title: What doctors worry about
Description: We worry about what our doctors will tell us — and so do they. Doctors, scientists and medical researchers weigh in on health care and better health practices.

Title: Our brains: predictably irrational
Description: The 3 pounds of jelly in our skulls allow us to reflect on our own consciousness — and to make counterintuitive, irrational decisions. These talks explore why.

Title: Maestros, if you please ... !
Description: These extraordinary maestros bring you into the world of writing and conducting music.

Title: War stories
Description: We need to talk about war. These powerful, crucial talks come from soldiers, politicians, journalists and others who've seen the reality of war firsthand.

Title: Climate change: Oh, it's real.
Description: We still have a lot to learn about climate change, about why it's happening and what that means. But one thing is clear: It's real, alright. These talks provide a primer on the issue of our times.

Title: Calling all sports fans
Description: Whether you love to swim, run, ski, shoot hoops or play cricket, these talks will make you wish you had a foam finger to hoist in the air.

Title: Ocean wonders
Description: Dive into the unexplored universe beneath the waves: the beautiful, fragile (and sometimes terrifying) world of the ocean.

Title: What makes you happy?
Description: Everyone wants to be happy. But how, exactly, does one go about it?  Here, psychologists, journalists, Buddhist monks and more gives answers that may surprise.

Title: Advice to help you be a great parent
Description: Kids don't come with a manual, and parents don't get grades to affirm they're doing things right. These talks speak to the complexities of parenthood, offering unusual insights and hard-won advice.

Title: Objects of desire
Description: An iconic painting. An ancient manuscript. A cylinder with 2600 years of history. Learn about artifacts and images that have intrigued humans for centuries, and why we find them so alluring.

Title: Making sense of too much data
Description: It's the age of Big Data. But what, exactly, do we do with all this information? These talks explore practical, ethical — and spectacularly visual — ways to understand near-infinite data.

Title: Are you there, God?
Description: For as many people as there are on Earth, there are as many answers to the question: Are you there, God? These talks offer a spectrum of personal perspectives on faith, from ardent atheists to devout believers.

Title: Top TED Talks of 2016
Description: Wonder which talks to get started on in 2016? A collection of hand-picked gems for your viewing pleasure.

Title: Most popular TED Talks of 2017
Description: What a year! These 14 talks challenged our perceptions of love, happiness, what the future will hold ... and, um, the very nature of reality itself.

Title: The paths and possibilities of police reform
Description: Thoughtful, actionable TED talks on how we might transform a seemingly impossible problem into a solvable one.

Title: 11 must-see TED Talks
Description: What is TED? This primer of 11 classic TED Talks show you the wide range of topics covered — and introduce you to beloved speakers like Amy Cuddy, Brené Brown, Sir Ken Robinson and Chimamanda Adichie. Find your next favorite talk ...

Title: How to survive following your passions
Description: So, you've decided to pursue your dreams. Go you! It'll be hard work, but well worth the effort. Throughout your quest, let these TED Talks reinvigorate your sense of purpose when times get tough.

Title: Talks by living legends
Description: These brilliant people have shaped their fields — from inventing the World Wide Web to changing the world of dance. They share their work in their own words.

Title: Can you believe your eyes?
Description: Magic tricks, optical illusions, death-defying feats, digital lies. Believe it or not.

Title: Little-known big history
Description: A collection of histories the textbooks left out ...

Title: Survivor’s wisdom
Description: Powerful, perspective-shifting talks on what it means to live courageously.

Title: How does my brain work?
Description: How exactly does the brain — a 3-pound snarl of nervous tissue — create inspired inventions, the feeling of hunger, the experience of beauty, the sense of self? Researchers at the edge of science explain ...

Title: How to be a better you
Description: Ready for a change? These well-researched (and heartfelt) talks offer ideas and inspiration for all aspects of your life, from creativity to vulnerability, from competitive sports to collaborative games.

Title: The most binge-worthy TED Talks
Description: A surprising collection of TED Talks to delight and ensnare you for hours and hours.

Title: How to be a great leader
Description: What makes a great leader? These TED Talks offer surprising, nuanced approaches on how to inspire and empower others to do their very best.

Title: 12 talks from authors
Description: These well-known writers weave beautiful words on the page ... and on the stage.

Title: The end of oil?
Description: It's the question of our generation: Can we find a sustainable alternative to oil? Scientists, inventors and activists present stern warnings and visionary solutions for the energy of tomorrow.

Title: Why we do the things we do
Description: Ever wondered, why did I just do that? These fascinating talks explain the hidden reasons why we do what we do.

Title: Music around the world
Description: Take a trip around the globe and enjoy music from all corners of the Earth.

Title: The issues at stake in the US election of 2016
Description: Relevant, informative talks to help you navigate the conversation surrounding the 2016 presidential election.

Title: When you need to take an intellectual snack break
Description: A selection of fascinating TED Talks for when you need to feed your intellectual curiosity (in 10 minutes or less).

Title: TED Talks for 20-somethings
Description: Twenty-somethings rejoice! From personal finance to finding your passion, these TED Talks can help you through your (first, second and possibly third) quarter-life crisis.

Title: Everything you thought ... was wrong
Description: 12 counterintuitive talks to flip your thinking on everything from shoes to aid organizations to the universe.

Title: The dark side of data
Description: Data can be used for good, harnessed for the betterment of society, but it can also be abused. Find out about some hidden not-so-sunny uses of Big Data.

Title: Work happier
Description: How to be happier at work? Start by focusing on happiness — not, surprisingly, on work. We learned this fun fact from Shawn Achor's TED Talk. So we asked Achor to choose some more talks he loves, about making work and life a happier place.

Title: What does the future look like?
Description: Visions of the future of everything from cars to the Internet to the human species.

Title: Weird facts about the human body
Description: The workings of the human body? An absolute marvel. And yet, kind of bizarre. The facts in these talks point to both conclusions.

Title: The quest to end poverty
Description: It's the challenge of our age: How do we end poverty? Hear ideas and results from economists, philanthropists, activists working — in labs and on the ground — to wipe it out.

Title: Talks to help you understand what's really going on in the world
Description: The headlines on the front page always change. But these talks — on the seismic phenomenon underlying them — will give you fresh insight.

Title: How music affects us
Description: Music is a fundamental aspect of humanity — so exactly how does it impact us? These talks offer a wonderful look at our fascinating relationship with the music we make.

Title: The power of the individual voice
Description: It only takes one voice to create change. Be inspired to take action through these talks by brave and passionate individuals.

Title: Earth, appreciated
Description: Our planet is a wonder, a perfectly improbable incubator for life. It’s also in danger because of our indifference. Reflections on both those truths.

Title: The pros and cons of digital life
Description: Our hyper-connected lives have been rewired for the digital age. These talks explore how the Internet and social media are shaping our relationships, personal lives and sense of self.

Title: TED’s how-to guide to everyday life
Description: Life is long, and so is this list. A treasure trove of how-tos (from tying your shoes to finding work you love) to bookmark, download and return to again and again.

Title: Check your assumptions
Description: Everyone makes snap judgments. These talks challenge the hidden biases we all hold — around looks, race, class, gender, language.

Title: Life is beautiful
Description: These talks will make your heart ache in the best of ways. Each is a wonderful reminder of the beautiful poignancy of life.

Title: Freedom rising

Title: Talks for band geeks
Description: If you were in the marching band, jazz ensemble or choir, music is a part of you — whether you still play or not. Let these talks tap into that.

Title: 10 talks by women that everyone should watch
Description: Color bravery. A headset for brainwaves. His/hers healthcare. 10 big, bold talks from female speakers.

Title: Counterintuitive career advice

Title: Jill Bolte Taylor: 10 talks on human nature

Title: For classical music lovers
Description: From Chopin to Handel and everything in between — immerse yourself in the world of classical music.

Description: Fascinating, little-known stories about some of the biggest happenings in history.

Title: Talks to inspire projects with kids
Description: These crafty talks will ignite passions, pique interests and introduce kids to the excitement of hands-on learning.

Title: The evolution of music
Description: How did music transform into what it is today? A brief journey through time, sound and rhythm.

Title: Brain thaw with TED Fellows
Description: Brain frozen? Thaw it out with this fun, unexpected blend of talks and performances by TED Fellows — updated regularly. It's sure to get your brain moving (and dancing) again.

Title: Talks that explain difficult topics to kids
Description: Sometimes, talking with kids about certain subjects is hard. We’re here for you with these gentle lead-ins to help get those tough conversations started.

Title: Graduation…now what?
Description: Great life advice for the moment after you throw your mortarboard in the air.

Title: Gorgeous, awe-inspiring images of Earth from above
Description: Get a bird's eye view of Earth's mesmerizing beauty, from the sky and outer space.

Title: Bobak Ferdowsi: On our home in the universe
Description: NASA engineer Bobak Ferdowsi helped the Curiosity rover land on Mars — and he's curated these talks that deepen our understanding of the world around us.

Title: Talks to help you (re)design your apartment
Description: Appreciate your space in new ways with these fun, insightful talks that will help guide you in redesigning the place you call home.

Title: TEDNYC Design Lab
Description: All about great design, these talks focus on solving problems while bringing beauty to the world. Learn more about the salon, curated by TED's own Chee Pearlman.

Title: Is it time for de-extinction?
Description: Is it time to bring back long-lost species? These talks tackle the possibility of a world where Jurassic Park doesn’t seem so science fiction.

Title: An ode to unsung heroes
Description: These talks honor the selfless and overall wonderful human beings who help us every day.

Title: Talks to help you manage stress
Description: Sometimes life can feel like a bit of a mess, but these talks are here to help you de-stress.

Title: So, you're on a boat
Description: Talks for when you find yourself in, near or around boats of any size.

Title: The harmful effects of online abuse
Description: A look at how the offline harm of online abuse is real and widespread with potentially severe consequences.

Title: The perfect lunchtime talks
Description: Need something smart to chew on? As you eat lunch, cue up these delightful talks, as invigorating for the mind as a cup of coffee.

Title: Talks to help you find the ideal employee
Description: Looking for the best of the best to join your organization? Fresh thinking on how to find the right fit.

Title: When school's out for the summer
Description: Keep the brain sharp and engaged with these talks that make it fun to avoid the summer slump.

Title: Fighting impostor syndrome
Description: You deserve much more than you think — that job you’ve been eyeing, the raise you want. It’s time that you convinced yourself. Let these talks help.

Title: Talks for aspiring rockstars
Description: Get ready to rock out with these awesome performances that have lit up the TED stage.

Title: What's the future of food?
Description: Scientists and entrepreneurs have been cooking up innovative ways to put food on our tables. What are they serving up next?

Title: Walk, walk, fashion baby
Description: Venture down the catwalk with these talks all about the creatively wild world of fashion.

Title: Get into your genes
Description: Try on these talks about the traits that make you who you are.

Title: Talks to watch when you have a big decision to make
Description: For when you need to stop biting your nails and just pick a direction.

Title: What's happening to the ocean?
Description: Are we turning the oceans into warm, noisy, uninhabitable bodies of acid? The short answer is, yes — but there's still hope.

Title: Sharks!
Description: Our talks featuring sharks — arguably one of the more misunderstood creatures of the deep blue sea.

Title: For the love of introverts
Description: A celebration of time spent in good company. (Sorry extroverts — we love you, too.)

Title: What comes after war?
Description: PTSD, isolation, depression ... These talks tackle the visible and invisible wounds left behind by violent conflict.

Title: Talks to inspire you to go to bed and get a good night's sleep
Description: Far better than counting sheep, these talks on the importance of sleep may well help you get your zzzzs tonight.

Title: Rebel designers
Description: Push the boundaries with these talks about individuals willing to break the rules in the name of good design.

Title: Poor design… and how to make it better
Description: When form and function don’t exactly match up, these speakers offer masterful advice on how to keep good design in mind. (Sorry, Pocatello.)

Title: Why we need bees
Description: Bees are nature’s tiny workers. These talks examine why they’re crucial to the earth and worth saving.

Title: Let’s redesign the medical experience!
Description: An exploration of what it would like if the medical industry practiced a more patient-first mentality.

Title: Talks that will make you think twice
Description: Everyday sights and experiences that are not as innocuous and innocent as they may seem.

Title: Talks for the fiber arts lover
Description: These speakers weave together some of our most interesting talks on the fine arts of knitting, crocheting and fabrics in general.

Title: Art made of unusual stuff
Description: Immerse yourself in the weirdly wonderful world of art made from unconventional materials.

Title: What comes after grief?
Description: Be inspired by these speakers who found comfort in transforming grief and sadness into action, art and progress.

Title: History, visualized
Description: A collection of talks that highlight the powerful impact of sharing history visually.

Title: The magic of the human voice
Description: From beat-boxing battles to a digital choir of 2000 people, these talks celebrate the beauty and versatility of the human voice.

Title: What’s really floating out in space?
Description: The answer is satellites, stars, planets, asteroids and maybe even aliens.

Title: How does time affect you?
Description: These talks explore why time may feel a little different for everyone and how to wrangle a little more for yourself.

Title: Talks on water
Description: Dive into these talks about water and humanity’s relationship with this life-sustaining liquid.

Title: Jamie Oliver: 5 talks that inspired me
Description: Jamie Oliver came to fame as the Naked Chef — now he's made it his mission to transform the way we feed ourselves and our children, through his cookbooks, TV shows and the Jamie Oliver Food Foundation. The 2010 TED Prize winner shares his 5 favorite talks.

Title: How to tap into our collective empathy
Description: These TED Talks advocate for creating bridges of compassion and understanding.

Title: All about the heart
Description: Get to know your heart a bit better with insightful talks on this powerful, life-sustaining organ.

Title: Art made of data
Description: Seeing patterns and creating beauty — data visualization has become an art form. Meet pioneering artists who use spreadsheets, archives and digital data as their paints and canvas.

Title: Lasers!
Description: Admit it, lasers are pretty cool. Discover the awesome, ingenious ways these beams of light are being used to fight against malaria and HIV, scan ancient monuments ... and even edit memory.

Title: Rethinking how we use the senses
Description: Fascinating and perspective-shifting, these talks demonstrate the ways the 5 senses are being used to build new windows into how we see the world and interact with our surroundings.

Title: The lights and sounds of the universe
Description: Find out what sound a black hole makes, if (possible) alien life is blocking star light and other astounding things happening in our galaxy — and beyond.

Title: Bizarre science
Description: Take a walk on the stranger side of science with these uncanny, yet fascinating talks.

Title: Let's end the silence around suicide
Description: It's easy to suffer in silence, not knowing what to say to whom. These brave, honest talks suggest ways to open up, talk about it and seek help — as well as ways to offer it.

Title: Talks to watch when student debt is getting you down
Description: You're not alone in the overwhelming sum that you carry with you. Explore what it means to be a university student in this era of massive debt, and the low-cost alternatives to battling this reality.

Title: Talks to watch during breakfast
Description: Illuminating, funny and awe-inspiring talks to start off your day.

Title: How we live now
Description: Traditional homes and living no more! Experience the different ways people exist in harmony with one another and their surroundings.

Title: Talks for cat lovers
Description: These talks feature some of our favorite feline friends talked about on the TED stage.

Title: Eye-opening undercover journalism
Description: These investigations into the dark underbelly of society shed light on some of the world’s most pressing issues.

Title: Things you've probably never noticed
Description: Wait, what's that? Did you see it? Bet you didn't. Check out these talks that'll help you see the intriguing details hiding in plain sight.

Title: Björk: 6 talks that are music to my ears
Description: Björk picks 6 TED Talks that she simply adores, from a mushroom burial suit to a virtual choir of thousands.

Title: Talks to watch if you have roommates
Description: Related or not, living under the same roof can be tough.

Title: How data can save lives
Description: An exploration of what we can do to save the world with the massive amounts of data collected every day.

Title: How the brain takes care of itself
Description: If the brain takes care of the body, how does the brain take care of itself? Find out the remarkable things the brain can do to stay in tiptop shape.

Title: Talks for when you're starting a new job
Description: Being the new person is never easy. Let these talks help you in walking into your workplace with your shoulders back and head held high.

Title: Smart kids’ life advice
Description: These young speakers encourage us to ask bold questions, think creatively and dream big. It’s spot-on life advice that adults may just want to listen to.

Title: The transformative power of street art
Description: Public art transforms spaces and connects people, revitalizing its surroundings. Immerse yourself in these talks that morph communities into masterpieces.

Title: Pets of the future
Description: Imagine a future home filled with robots in the likeness of dogs, cats and even dinosaurs ...

Title: The mysteries of the deep sea
Description: Explore endless waters with these captivating talks that shine some (literal) light on what’s going in the deepest, darkest parts of our oceans.

Title: Talks on remembering those we've lost
Description: The pain of personal loss, war and conflict is universal. These speakers share large and small ways to remember those lost even long after they're gone.

Title: #Goals
Description: Counterintuitive advice that will help you set and achieve your goals for the short-term, long-term and those moments in between.

Title: There's an app for that
Description: Everyone makes the joke, but it's true. Here's a selection of interesting apps and the inspiration behind them.

Title: Charming talks for a boost on a bad day
Description: Bad days happen to good people. Here are talks guaranteed to help cheer you up.

Title: How to understand your inner potential
Description: No one takes the same life path to personal success. These talks can help you examine and identify the unique passions and perspectives that make you, you.

Title: TED Residency Talks
Description: The TED Residency program is an incubator for breakthrough ideas. Curious about what goes down at TED HQ? Check out  ted.com/residency for more information (or to even become a Resident yourself).

Title: Dude, where's my driverless car?
Description: Let's be honest, flying cars are still a ways into the future. Until then, learn about the extraordinary lengths we've come with cars that drive themselves.

Title: Talks to save you time at work — so you can focus on what you love
Description: For all those days you've ever checked the clock and thought, Where did the last hour go? These talks share helpful hacks for stealing back a few seconds, minutes or even hours from your busy workday.

Title: Why you should document your life
Description: Time can pass in the blink of an eye. These talks underscore the importance of not just stopping to smell the roses, but also taking a photo or two while you're at it.

Title: Kids, teens and their great big ideas
Description: Amazing inventions, activism and tons of genius delivered by an awesome group of kids and teens.

Title: The power of asking
Description: These talks reveal that some things are more within your grasp than you may think, especially if you ask.

Title: How to navigate questionable information
Description: Inaccuracies can be difficult to spot. See the difference between fact and fiction, and learn to spot the gray areas with these informative talks.

Title: Diane von Furstenberg's 4 favorite TED Talks
Description: The legendary fashion designer — who created the wrap dress and remains an icon in the industry (she's also President of the Council of Fashion Designers of America) — picks the 5 TED talks that have inspired her most.

Title: For parents who have lost a child
Description: Losing children to illness, disease or acts of violence is devastating and endlessly difficult to cope with. These talks come from parents who have experienced such loss and found a way to make it through.

Title: Short talks to watch during your coffee break
Description: Got just enough time for a coffee, but in need of a mental pick-me-up? These short, yet riveting talks may just do the trick.

Title: How do you create new words?
Description: 4 reasons why you shouldn't be afraid to make up new words (no matter how ridiculous they may sound).

Title: Inside the mind of psychopaths
Description: An illuminating, if not slightly chilling, exploration of what makes a psychopath.

Title: New thoughts on addiction
Description: These talks take a new, fresh perspective while exploring the epidemic of addiction.

Title: Building introspective spaces
Description: A thoughtful walk-through on what it takes to design spaces for quiet moments of reflection.

Title: Seeing sound and hearing color
Description: Keep your ears and eyes wide open for the several different ways you can interact with sound and color.

Title: Fascinating windows into humanity
Description: A collection of studies and photography series that showcase the intrigue, beauty and diversity of human life.

Title: Grow your own stuff
Description: You’ve heard of ‘do it yourself,’ but what about ‘grow it yourself?’ Enjoy these quirky talks full of possibilities.

Title: Let's talk crap
Description: Why basic sanitation should be a right, not a privilege.

Title: Young inventors who are changing how we stay healthy
Description: These speakers — all under 21 when they gave their talks — have big ideas for our health. Meet young people who are taking on cancer, asthma, injuries, even Alzheimer’s with a bold new approach.

Title: 8 TED Talks selected by Shah Rukh Khan
Description: Please enjoy these talks that I hope capture your heart as they did mine. If you love them, then please see and explore more with TED Talks India.

Title: Life lessons from the four elements
Description: We have much to learn from the natural world — from little lessons to perspective-shifting wisdom.

Title: The race for your attention
Description: Attention: everybody wants some — social media, tech companies and more. Watch these talks to better understand the ways these entities try and get on your radar.

Title: How perfectionism fails us
Description: Why it's best to celebrate the little wins and imperfect moments alongside the big successes to combat our fear of failure.

Title: Searching for knowledge across disciplines
Description: What can people in seemingly unrelated fields learn from each other? These astonishing talks highlight the importance of searching for answers where you may least expect them.

Title: Short talks for parents who are short on time but starved for intellectual stimulation
Description: You aren't sleeping. You barely have time to eat, let alone peruse TED Talks. Here, talks under six minutes that will give you a quick dose of inspiration.

Title: The issue of homelessness
Description: A basic primer on some of the hows and whys, solutions and struggles surrounding the conversation on homelessness.

Title: The inherent bias in our technology
Description: These talks reveal how our technology often reflects the unconscious biases and prejudices we hold.

Title: The air around us
Description: It's invisible, vital and life-sustaining. Get to know air, our ubiquitous and ever-present (if not a little gassy) neighbor.

Title: Why it's (sometimes) good to be bored
Description: How being bored can lead to new possibilities, better ideas and even an extra shot of creativity.

Title: Talks to kickstart your next career
Description: These talks will inspire a professional renaissance and give you the courage to start along a new career path.

Title: Dave Eggers: 4 talks that are spot-on
Description: As Dave Eggers says, The best TED Talks make sense of complicated ideas and trends, and have an elegant simplicity to them. It’s plenty of time to get across a clear and bold idea.” Below, his notes on 4 great talks.

Title: Using art history to examine modern day
Description: Observe our modern times through the lens of art history with these compelling, masterful talks.

Title: The fight against Alzheimer’s and dementia
Description: Alzheimer’s and dementia are a heart-breaking reality for millions across the world. Find out what inventors and scientists on the cutting edge of medical research are doing to combat this neurological puzzle.

Title: Talks to watch when you need five minutes of peace
Description: Calming, short talks to watch when you just want to peace out for a bit.

Title: Deep studies of humanity
Description: Fascinating, insightful talks on what it means to be human and live a good life.

Title: Super nerdy talks about sports
Description: You love sports stats and rewatch classic games for the nuance. These talks on the math, science and evolution of sports are for you.

Title: Wacky, weird art made by AI
Description: Welcome to the new frontier in art and creativity — and it's not human.

Title: How space technology can change life on Earth
Description: Sure, we're looking beyond the planet to other worlds we may one day inhabit — but a lot of this technology we've developed can be used for the good of the Earth, too.

Title: Talks on folklore
Description: These talks explore some of the myths, folklore and fairytales that (once upon a time) explained the unexplainable.

Title: The mystery and wonder of stars
Description: Zoom into the strange wonder and potential of stars in our universe.

Title: Things that build themselves
Description: If you build it, they will come... But what happens when robots, buildings and other marvels can build themselves? These talks explore this (increasingly real) reality.

Title: Get paid what you’re worth
Description: You know your worth, watch these talks and get paid the proper value of your skills.

Title: The big problem with fashion — and how to fix it
Description: The fashion industry has a big carbon footprint. How can we find a sustainable solution that fits?

Title: What can robots teach us about being human?
Description: Robots reflect their creators: Us. Counterintuitive and insightful, these robots show us glimmers into what it means to be human.

Title: CrashCourse
Description: Tons of awesome courses in one awesome channel! Nicole Sweeney teaches you sociology, Carrie Anne Philbin teaches you computer science, Craig Benzine teaches film history, and Mike Rugnetta is teaching mythology!   Check out the playlists for past courses in physics, philosophy, games, economics, U.S. government and politics, astronomy, anatomy & physiology, world history, biology, literature, ecology, chemistry, psychology, and U.S. history.  Help support Crash Course at Patreon.com/CrashCourse.

Title: TED-Ed
Description: TED-Ed’s commitment to creating lessons worth sharing is an extension of TED’s mission of spreading great ideas. Within TED-Ed’s growing library of TED-Ed animations, you will find carefully curated educational videos, many of which represent collaborations between talented educators and animators nominated through the TED-Ed website (ed.ted.com).  Want to suggest an idea for a TED-Ed animation or get involved with TED-Ed? Visit our website at: http://ed.ted.com/get_involved.  Also, consider donating to us on Patreon! By doing so, you directly support our mission and receive some pretty awesome rewards: https://www.patreon.com/teded  For more information on using TED for commercial purposes (e.g. employee learning, in a film, or in an online course), please submit a Media Request using this link: https://media-requests.ted.com/

Title: TEDMED
Description: TEDMED bridges the gap between science and the public by finding and sharing stories that inform, inspire, engage and provoke action across a broad, passionate community both inside and outside of health and medicine. TEDMED values inclusiveness, multi-disciplinary collaboration and diversity in its mission to catalyze a healthier world.  Our annual event brings the world together to focus on what’s new and important in health and medicine. We forge partnerships with industry leaders, medical research institutions, think tanks, government agencies and foundations, to ensure that cutting-edge biomedical thinking, innovation in healthcare and large scale global public health opportunities are shared across disciplines and made accessible to the public at large.  Year-round, TEDMED engages a community of dedicated change-makers in dynamic conversations through social media, TEDMED Talks and a variety of programmatic efforts leveraging dynamic partnerships.

Title: C'est pas sorcier
Description: C'est pas sorcier, la chaîne officielle.  La science évolue sans cesse, certaines données chiffrées peuvent avoir changé depuis la réalisation de cette émission, certaines découvertes ont pu être faites : comme tout journaliste multipliez vos sources d'information.  Retrouvez le magazine de la science et de la découverte, ludique, accessible dès le plus jeune âge et pour toute la famille !  Retrouvez C'est pas sorcier sur http://pluzzvad.francetv.fr : cinéma, séries, docus, spectacles, jeunesse en vidéo à la demande. Et en ce moment, découvrez le magazine officiel C'est pas sorcier aux caisses des super et hypermarchés, pour tout savoir sur le Sahara, Bollywood, les QR codes, les mammifères et le slackline avec des expériences et des jeux.

Title: Deus Ex Silicium
Description: DEUS EX SILICIUM est le premier projet francophone de chaine d'électronique dédiée à la science des semi-conducteurs et à leurs très nombreuses applications. Imaginée pour les ingénieurs, hackeurs, amateurs, étudiants, geeks ou passionnés de technologie, elle est diffusée en fullHD sur Youtube et Dailymotion.  ---------------------  DEUS EX SILICIUM is the very first french-speaking Youtube channel about electronics engineering dedicated to semiconductors and their numerous applications. Designed for engineers, hackers, hobbyists, students, geeks and technology lovers, it's broadcasted fullHD (in french only, but subtitles are coming) on Youtube and Dailymotion.

Title: DirtyBiology
Description: Tu ne voulais pas le savoir, mais maintenant c'est trop tard ! Des vidéos de science sur des sujets mindfuck, crades, ou juste rigolos. Parfois on parle de biologie aussi.

Title: e-penser
Description: Pourquoi bâiller, c'est contagieux ? Qu'est-ce qu'un trou noir ? Comment se forment les arc-en-ciel ? Aristote a-t-il eu raison au moins une fois de son vivant ? Pourquoi 42 ? Docteur qui ? A quoi a vraiment servi Einstein ? Le boson de Higgs ?! Le lolcat de Schrödinger...  Restez curieux, et prenez le temps d'e-penser.

Title: Hygiène Mentale
Description: Si on avait un vrai système éducatif dans ce pays, on y donnerait des cours d'Autodéfense-Intellectuelle  Zététique , Scepticisme, Etude scientifique des phénomènes dites paranormaux . Title: Le blob (universcience.tv)
Description: La Cité des sciences et de l’industrie et le Palais de la découverte lancent le blob, un nouveau média numérique de culture scientifique, gratuit et sans publicité. Ce média se décline en un site web intégrant une plateforme de plusieurs milliers de vidéos en accès libre, une chaine YouTube et des comptes Facebook, Twitter et Instagram. L’offre originale de ce nouveau média : une nouvelle vidéo à la une chaque jour, un fonds VOD en accès libre, un fil d’actualité scientifique quotidien et des enquêtes mensuelles sur les grands sujets contemporains.

Title: Maths et tiques
Description: Professeur de mathématiques en lycée (Académie de Strasbourg), je partage : - une chaîne YouTube : près de 1500 vidéos pour t'aider à t'améliorer en maths. - un site www.maths-et-tiques.fr : des cours complets, des exercices, des curiosités autour des maths.  Les mathématiques sont ma passion, mon hobby, mes loisirs, mes vacances, ma vie ! Je ne compte jamais mes heures à créer des vidéos, écrire des cours, des exercices, ... je le fais parce que cela me plait.  Les gains générés par les pubs me permettent d’effectuer des dons réguliers aux associations (Restos du Cœur, Unicef, Fond. des Hôpitaux de France, Emmaüs...). Objectif sur l'année 2020 = 20 000 €.  Site officiel : http://www.maths-et-tiques.fr Twitter : https://twitter.com/mtiques Facebook : https://www.facebook.com/mathsettiques/ Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/yvanmonka/

Title: Video Mpya za Ubongo Kids!
Description: Angalia video mpya za Ubongo Kids kwa mwaka 2017!  Jamani! Mwaka huu, Ubongo Kids ni ZAIDI ya hisabati na sayansi! Msimu huu si KAMA ULIVYOZOEA!  Ubongo Kids MPYA inamjenga mwanao, ikimpa fikra komavu zitakazomwezesha kutambua kusudi lake masomoni na maishani!  Njoo nasi Kokotoa, ukajifunze kutumia uwezo na utashi wako kusuluhisha changamoto zinazokukabili ili ufike pale utakapo!  Msimu wa 3 wa Ubongo Kids utakuandaa kifikra, ukichochea uwezo wako wa kung’amua matatizo na kuyatafutia ufumbuzi.  Ubongo Kids ni mfululizo wa hadithi za kusisimua zilizo katika mfumo wa elimu-burudani kwa ajili ya watoto wa miaka 7 hadi 13, zikitumia nyimbo na maudhui ya Kiafrika kuwafundisha hisabati na sayansi!   Katuni hii mahususi ya elimu inaandaliwa na Ubongo Learning, ambao pia ni watengenezaji wa kipindi murua ya AkiliandMe inayowaandaa watoto wa miaka 3-6 kwa ajili ya kwenda shule!  Tazama Ubongo Kids kila Jumamosi na Jumapili saa 3 asubuhi kupitia TBC1! Pata pia  webisodes zetu zote kupitia: http://www.ubongokids.com

Title: Ubongo Kids + Amplify/ IDEO.org | Collecting Caregivers' Stories
Description: Videos co-produced by Ubongo and IDEO.org to prompt discussion and story sharing about caregiver experiences in Tanzania.  Who do you ask for nutritional advice for your infant?  Do mothers and fathers have different roles in parenting school aged children? What do you do to teach your child life skills?  We explored these questions and more, through this interactive TV + call-in segments broadcast across Tanzania!  To learn more about Ubongo visit www.ubongo.org
